video.title: Star Trek: Voyager
video.synopsis: On Voyager's 75-year journey back to earth, the crew comes in contact with unknown species as they're drawn closer to a mysterious quadrant of space.

episodes.synopsis: While pursuing the trail of Maquis rebels, a newly commissioned Starfleet ship gets pulled to the far side of the galaxy.
episodes.title: Caretaker: Parts 1 & 2

episodes.synopsis: Voyager has set a course for home, repairs are underway, and it's time to pick personnel to fill vital crew positions.
episodes.title: Parallax

episodes.synopsis: The Voyager crew discovers a planet that recently suffered a horrific catastrophe.
episodes.title: Time and Again

episodes.synopsis: With dilithium reserves running low, Janeway follows Neelix's advice and proceeds to the nearest known supply.
episodes.title: Phage

episodes.synopsis: With power reserves running low, the crew of Voyager alters its course.
episodes.title: The Cloud

episodes.synopsis: The Voyager crew detects a wormhole in the Delta quadrant and immediately changes course with hopes it will provide passage home.
episodes.title: Eye of the Needle

episodes.synopsis: The Baneans wrongfully convict Tom Paris of murder.
episodes.title: Ex Post Facto

episodes.synopsis: A Voyager sensor scan reveals what seems to be a previously undiscovered chemical element in a group of asteroids.
episodes.title: Emanations

episodes.synopsis: The crew encounters a hedonistic alien race with the ability to travel through the galaxy at will.
episodes.title: Prime Factors

episodes.synopsis: Voyager answers a distress call from a Kazon-Nistrim ship to find all but one of the crew dead in an explosion.
episodes.title: State of Flux

episodes.synopsis: After Harry Kim disappears during his Beowulf holonovel program, Chakotay and Tuvok are sent to investigate and they disappear.
episodes.title: Heroes and Demons

episodes.synopsis: Energy beings from a nebula displace Chakotay's consciousness from his body.
episodes.title: Cathexis

episodes.synopsis: Paris, Torres and Durst are imprisoned by the Vidiians.
episodes.title: Faces

episodes.synopsis: Neelix is diagnosed with a fatal illness by a Haakonian named Ma'Bor Jetrel.
episodes.title: Jetrel

episodes.synopsis: While Voyager's mixed Starfleet-Maquis crew seems to be working out, a few rogue Maquis are fighting the integration.
episodes.title: Learning Curve

episodes.synopsis: Voyager answers an ancient SOS distress and finds eight humans -- including Amelia Earhart -- in cryo-stasis on a nearby planet.
episodes.title: The 37's

episodes.synopsis: Chakotay is captured by a young Kazon who is undergoing a manhood ritual.
episodes.title: Initiations

episodes.synopsis: The program for the Emergency Medical Hologram is activated due to what the computer describes as a ship-wide emergency.
episodes.title: Projections

episodes.synopsis: Voyager encounters new life forms that have a very unusual attraction to the ship.
episodes.title: Elogium

episodes.synopsis: Harry Kim wakes up in San Francisco having never been assigned to Voyager, which Starfleet considers lost.
episodes.title: Non Sequitur

episodes.synopsis: Voyager encounters a non-corporeal, sentient, space-dwelling life form which is interested in learning more about the ship and its people.
episodes.title: Twisted

episodes.synopsis: After a disagreement, Neelix and Paris are trapped on an alien planet and must work together so that they and their alien baby ward can survive.
episodes.title: Parturition

episodes.synopsis: The Voyager crew enters a new region of space and begins to see hallucinations. The Captain sees her holonovel characters come to life.
episodes.title: Persistence of Vision

episodes.synopsis: Finding a familiar cultural symbol on an away mission, Chakotay connects with an experience he had as a child and tries to contact his spirit people.
episodes.title: Tattoo

episodes.synopsis: Ten months after the Caretaker stranded Voyager in the Delta Quadrant, the ship encounters the alien's mate and a station full of Ocampa.
episodes.title: Cold Fire

episodes.synopsis: After the Kazon steal some Federation technology, Chakotay goes after them on his own and is captured.
episodes.title: Maneuvers

episodes.synopsis: Disguised while on an away mission, Capt. Janeway is rescued by a man who thinks that she is his daughter.
episodes.title: Resistance

episodes.synopsis: Voyager finds an automated life-form adrift in space. When B'Elanna Torres reactivates it, the unit realizes she may be able to build more.
episodes.title: Prototype

episodes.synopsis: Janeway tries to make an alliance with a Kazon sect for their own protection and so they can continue their journey through the Delta Quadrant.
episodes.title: Alliances

episodes.synopsis: After finding a type of dilithium that can survive at a higher temperatures, Tom Paris attempts to cross the transwarp threshold.
episodes.title: Threshold

episodes.synopsis: Tuvok investigates the murder of a Voyager engineer. Former Maquis and Betazoid Lon Suder confesses to the murder and offers no explanation.
episodes.title: Meld

episodes.synopsis: Voyager comes across a ship that has been destroyed, and upon investigation they discover that B'Elanna Torres is responsible.
episodes.title: Dreadnought

episodes.synopsis: While Voyager investigates a comet, the crew accidentally releases a member of the "Q continuum" who has been imprisoned for over 300 years.
episodes.title: Death Wish

episodes.synopsis: The Doctor saves a Vidiian dying from the Phage by placing her consciousness in a holographic body -- and he thinks he's falling in love with her.
episodes.title: Lifesigns

episodes.synopsis: Paris leaves Voyager and joins a Talaxian space convoy. Neelix helps smoke out the crewmember who has been passing Federation secrets to the Kazon.
episodes.title: Investigations

episodes.synopsis: A "spatial scission" causes Voyager to be duplicated. One of the Voyagers is under heavy attack from the Vidiians while the other remains impervious.
episodes.title: Deadlock

episodes.synopsis: Tuvok crashes on a planet where he finds some children who know that they are all going to die.
episodes.title: Innocence

episodes.synopsis: Voyager finds a group of people connected in stasis chambers and something has gone terribly wrong.
episodes.title: The Thaw

episodes.synopsis: Tuvok and Neelix are on an alien planet collecting examples of flora but when they attempt to beam back up there's a malfunction with the transporter.
episodes.title: Tuvix

episodes.synopsis: Capt. Janeway and Chakotay contract an incurable virus and they'll only survive if they stay on a planet which negates the effects of the disease.
episodes.title: Resolutions

episodes.synopsis: The Kazon seize Voyager and strand the crew on a desolate primitive planet. Only Paris, Suder and The Doctor are on board Voyager to retake the ship.
episodes.title: Basics: Part 1

episodes.synopsis: The Kazon take over Voyager and strand the crew on a desolate planet. Only Tom Paris, Lon Suder and The Doctor can retake the ship.
episodes.title: Basics: Part 2

episodes.synopsis: Capt. Janeway participates in a mind-meld with Tuvok, reliving his experiences on the SS Excelsior under the command of Capt. Sulu.
episodes.title: Flashback

episodes.synopsis: Tom Paris and Harry Kim are wrongly convicted of a terrorist bombing. Even though Janeway captures the true criminals, Tom and Harry are imprisoned.
episodes.title: The Chute

episodes.synopsis: Voyager is attacked by swarms of tiny spaceships. The Doctor is losing his memory, and Torres activates a program run by a familiar hologram.
episodes.title: The Swarm

episodes.synopsis: After meeting two Ferengis who have set themselves up as gods on a primitive planet, the Voyager crew plans to use a nearby wormhole to return home.
episodes.title: False Profits

episodes.synopsis: Lt. Torres starts having vivid dreams about another life, another love and another planet.
episodes.title: Remember

episodes.synopsis: After Kes is injured by an energy beam on a planet's sacred ground, Janeway must undergo a spiritual quest in order to save her life.
episodes.title: Sacred Ground

episodes.synopsis: When a timeship is thrown into the 20th century with the Voyager, the crew finds a company that has benefited from the future technology in 1996.
episodes.title: Future's End: Part 1

episodes.synopsis: Henry Starling made a fortune by looting 29th-century technology from the crashed timeship, and is planning a trip into the future to feed his greed.
episodes.title: Future's End: Part 2

episodes.synopsis: A dying warlord takes over Kes's body and is determined to reclaim his home planet.
episodes.title: Warlord

episodes.synopsis: After Q's death in its last meeting with Voyager, a new Q must be produced -- and the mischievous Q known to the Enterprise wants Janeway as his mate.
episodes.title: The Q and the Grey

episodes.synopsis: After returning from a first contact mission, Janeway, Neelix and the Doctor must retake Voyager from an infestation of microorganisms.
episodes.title: Macrocosm

episodes.synopsis: The Voyager heads into a section of space that Neelix has no knowledge of, so he tries to obtain a map of it from a less-than-reputable friend.
episodes.title: Fair Trade

episodes.synopsis: Harry Kim finds himself in love with Marayna, a character from Neelix's Polynesian resort holodeck program.
episodes.title: Alter Ego

episodes.synopsis: Chakotay and Janeway crash on a planet and are are stuck inside a time loop in which Janeway dies.
episodes.title: Coda

episodes.synopsis: Ensign Vorik undergoes the Vulcan mating ritual. The strong chemical imbalance affects B'Elanna Torres as well, leading her to irrational behavior.
episodes.title: Blood Fever

episodes.synopsis: Chakotay finds a planet of unassimilated Borg drones from all over the galaxy.
episodes.title: Unity

episodes.synopsis: The Doctor incorporates the personalities of several historical figures into his programming. B'Elanna warns him the results could be unfavorable.
episodes.title: Darkling

episodes.synopsis: Neelix and Tuvok get trapped on the surface of a planet being bombarded by asteroids. Tuvok's negative attitude begins to get on Neelix's nerves.
episodes.title: Rise

episodes.synopsis: Kim begins experiencing bizarre DNA changes and instinctively leads Voyager to a planet whose inhabitants claim Kim is really a member of their race.
episodes.title: Favorite Son

episodes.synopsis: Nearing death, Kes experiences parts of her life moving backward through time. The Doctor develops an experimental procedure to extend Kes's lifespan.
episodes.title: Before and After

episodes.synopsis: The Doctor creates a holographic family, but B'Elanna thinks the simulation is too "nice." She makes alterations to make the program more accurate.
episodes.title: Real Life

episodes.synopsis: A Saurian scientist finds the remains of a Voyager crewman who died on the planet where the crew was exiled by the Kazon during the episode "Basics."
episodes.title: Distant Origin

episodes.synopsis: One by one, Voyager's crew is being replaced by strangers, and the replacements don't know why they are there.
episodes.title: Displaced

episodes.synopsis: Members of the Voyager crew clandestinely participate in a hidden holodeck program where the ship's Maquis members stage an insurrection.
episodes.title: Worst Case Scenario

episodes.synopsis: About to enter Borg space, the Voyager crew discover a threat so devastating that even the Borg cannot deal with it.
episodes.title: Scorpion: Part 1

episodes.synopsis: Voyager finds a solution to combat the invader of Borg space. All Janeway asks is free passage through their territory and she'll share knowledge.
episodes.title: Scorpion: Part 2

episodes.synopsis: Seven of Nine, the Borg drone that Voyager severed from the collective, tries to resist as her natural human physiology tries to regenerate.
episodes.title: The Gift

episodes.synopsis: The Klingon holiday known as Day Of Honor comes and B'Elanna decides to embrace her Klingon heritage and participate in a series of ritual tests.
episodes.title: Day of Honor

episodes.synopsis: Commander Chakotay's shuttle is hit by enemy crossfire and crashes on a planet in the midst of a war.
episodes.title: Nemesis

episodes.synopsis: Voyager receives a distress call from a survivor on a damaged ship. When learning the survivor is a hologram, The Doctor joins B'Elanna on the ship.
episodes.title: Revulsion

episodes.synopsis: Janeway is trying to gain passage through a region of space owned by a cautious and xenophobic race of aliens.
episodes.title: The Raven

episodes.synopsis: A string of bizarre illnesses afflicts Voyager. The Doctor and Seven of Nine uncover a team of alien researchers performing medical experiments.
episodes.title: Scientific Method

episodes.synopsis: Voyager comes across a Krenim timeship that is wiping whole species from existence by changing the existing timeline.
episodes.title: Year of Hell: Part 1

episodes.synopsis: A year after Voyager encounters a Krenim time ship, a badly damaged Voyager with a skeleton crew leads an armada of interplanetary ships against them.
episodes.title: Year of Hell: Part 2

episodes.synopsis: Voyager visits a planet with a telepathic race that outlaws negative thoughts, and B'Elanna is charged with releasing an angry thought.
episodes.title: Random Thoughts

episodes.synopsis: While Janeway is visiting her da Vinci holodeck program, Voyager is mugged by a transporter. They steal everything from the main computer core.
episodes.title: Concerning Flight

episodes.synopsis: Neelix experiences a crisis of faith when, after being dead for nearly 19 hours, Seven of Nine revives him using her Borg technology.
episodes.title: Mortal Coil

episodes.synopsis: The Voyager crew are assaulted in the form of nightmares. An alien species, functioning only in a dream world, traps the crew in a shared dream.
episodes.title: Waking Moments

episodes.synopsis: Using an alien communications net, Voyager sends The Doctor to the Federation ship USS Prometheus only to find that it has been taken by Romulans.
episodes.title: Message in a Bottle

episodes.synopsis: Voyager starts to receive news from home, both good and bad. They also encounter the Hirogens, who only live to hunt and have their sights on Voyager.
episodes.title: Hunters

episodes.synopsis: Helping a wounded Hirogen, Janeway finds that their prey has boarded Voyager: a member of species 8472.
episodes.title: Prey

episodes.synopsis: Seven of Nine claims to have been assaulted by the arms trader who just sold new technology to Voyager.
episodes.title: Retrospect

episodes.synopsis: After Voyager is captured by the Hirogens, the ship is turned into a massive holodeck so that the Hirogens can hunt members of the crew.
episodes.title: The Killing Game: Part 1

episodes.synopsis: Janeway and the crew must retake Voyager from the Hirogens.
episodes.title: The Killing Game: Part 2

episodes.synopsis: Bored with his daily routine, Tom Paris finds a refreshing friendship with a visiting alien willing to share a new method of propulsion with Voyager.
episodes.title: Vis a Vis

episodes.synopsis: Voyager's sensor detect a rare particle theoretically capable of damaging subspace and nullifying warp travel.
episodes.title: The Omega Directive

episodes.synopsis: An alien woman requests asylum aboard Voyager, stating she has been aboard recently and she and Chakotay fell in love.
episodes.title: Unforgettable

episodes.synopsis: When The Doctor's backup module is found, his program is brought on-line for the first time in 700 years.
episodes.title: Living Witness

episodes.synopsis: Desperate to replenish the ship's power resources, Voyager seeks out a duranium signature on a class "Y" -- a.k.a. "Demon Class" -- planet.
episodes.title: Demon

episodes.synopsis: An unavoidable poisonous nebula forces the entire crew into stasis chambers -- all except the unaffected Doctor and Seven of Nine.
episodes.title: One

episodes.synopsis: An alien translator by the name of Arturis is able to finally decode the Starfleet message received by Voyager five months ago.
episodes.title: Hope and Fear

episodes.synopsis: Crew morale hits an all-time low when Voyager must spend two years crossing an expanse devoid of any star systems or signs of life.
episodes.title: Night

episodes.synopsis: After an away-mission shuttle is caught in a blast, the Doctor's mobile emitter is infected with Seven's nanoprobes.
episodes.title: Drone

episodes.synopsis: To cope with the loss of her Alpha Quadrant Maquis friends, B'Elanna secretly participates in several dangerous holodeck programs.
episodes.title: Extreme Risk

episodes.synopsis: The crew discovers a simulation of Starfleet Headquarters being run by Species 8472, the enemy they helped the Borg defeat in the episode "Scorpion."
episodes.title: In the Flesh

episodes.synopsis: The Delta Flyer crash-lands after encountering an ion storm. Voyager desperately tries to rescue Tuvok, Paris and a badly injured Ensign Wildman.
episodes.title: Once Upon a Time

episodes.synopsis: A miscalculation by Ensign Kim causes a fatal crash during Voyager's first test with slipstream travel.
episodes.title: Timeless

episodes.synopsis: Voyager comes in contact with Borg technology that causes Seven of Nine to display multiple personalities.
episodes.title: Infinite Regress

episodes.synopsis: An injured cytoplasmic life-form attaches itself to B'Elanna, tapping into her body like a parasite.
episodes.title: Nothing Human

episodes.synopsis: In a letter to his father, Tom Paris tells the story of the events leading up to his demotion to Ensign and his sentence to 30 days in Voyager's brig.
episodes.title: Thirty Days

episodes.synopsis: Voyager moves through a sector controlled by a race that is suspicious of telepathic lifeforms. The crew develops a novel approach to pass safely.
episodes.title: Counterpoint

episodes.synopsis: The Doctor uncovers evidence that his memory was erased 18 months ago. Nearly all traces of a fateful away mission have been deleted.
episodes.title: Latent Image

episodes.synopsis: While Paris and Kim are running their "Captain Proton" holodeck program, Voyager gets caught in a layer of subspace that is home to photonic aliens.
episodes.title: Bride of Chaotica

episodes.synopsis: A Voyager shuttle manned by Tuvok, Paris and the Doctor is pulled into a subspace gravity well and crashes on a Class D planet that exists within it.
episodes.title: Gravity

episodes.synopsis: Voyager discovers what seems to be a wormhole leading to the Alpha Quadrant and home. Images of Earth and letters from family elates the crew.
episodes.title: Bliss

episodes.synopsis: The Voyager crew trains to raid a Borg ship. Meanwhile, two years after being liberated, Seven of Nine rejoins the Borg, seemingly of her own will.
episodes.title: Dark Frontier: Parts 1 & 2

episodes.synopsis: Voyager encounters xenophobic nomads, at space for 400 years, with shipwide malfunctions. The crew's offer to help leads to serious consequences.
episodes.title: The Disease

episodes.synopsis: A respite is in order, but a mysterious force is affecting the very fabric of Voyager. To solve the mystery, the crew must retrace their steps.
episodes.title: Course: Oblivion

episodes.synopsis: Voyager gets trapped in "chaotic space," a kind of Bermuda Triangle, where sensors are useless and a straight line sends the ship running in circles.
episodes.title: The Fight

episodes.synopsis: Voyager is sought after by the Hazari, unyielding bounty hunters of the Delta Quadrant. A group of problem-solvers offers a way to outwit the Hazari.
episodes.title: Think Tank

episodes.synopsis: After answering a Malon freighter's distress call, Torres, Neelix, Chakotay and the surviving Malon have six hours to stop a theta-radiation fallout.
episodes.title: Juggernaut

episodes.synopsis: Voyager makes first contact with the Kadi, a race with a strict social protocol. Meanwhile, Seven gets lessons in dating from the Doctor.
episodes.title: Someone to Watch Over Me

episodes.synopsis: The Voyager crew members swap stories of their family histories. Janeway is most proud of her ancestor Shannon O'Donnell, a celebrated astronaut.
When Voyager is destroyed, Capt. Braxton of the 29th-century timeship Relativity contacts Seven of Nine to learn who planted the temporal disruptor.
episodes.title: Relativity

episodes.synopsis: An alien missile that possesses artificial intelligence begins to terrorize the Voyager crew.
episodes.title: Warhead

episodes.synopsis: Voyager encounters the starship Equinox, a heavily damaged Starfleet vessel trapped in the Delta Quadrant by the same alien who brought Voyager there.
episodes.title: Equinox: Part 1

episodes.synopsis: Temporarily shielded from the alien attack, Janeway's first priority is to find the Equinox, stop Ransom and recover Seven of Nine.
episodes.title: Equinox: Part 2

episodes.synopsis: Eager for culture exchange and friendly contact at a space outpost, Janeway grants shore leave to her crew and rolls out the welcome mat for visitors.
episodes.title: Survival Instinct

episodes.synopsis: When an ion storm hits her shuttle, B'Elanna is injured and slips into a coma, during which she envisions Klingons killing her and her crewmates.
episodes.title: Barge of the Dead

episodes.synopsis: The Doctor's experiment with daydreaming spins out of control when an alien race taps into his thoughts and compromises his program.
episodes.title: Tinker, Tenor, Doctor, Spy

episodes.synopsis: The crew discovers a space-age junkyard near their course. Later, Voyager -- desperate for supplies -- finds an eager trader.
episodes.title: Alice

episodes.synopsis: Returning from an away mission, the Delta Flyer is boarded -- and Tuvok is assaulted by a cloaked alien from a xenophobic race called the Ba'Neth.
episodes.title: Riddles

episodes.synopsis: Voyager is pulled into a subspace corridor, traveling 200 light-years until pushed out by the Turei -- who claim ownership of the labyrinth.
episodes.title: Dragon's Teeth

episodes.synopsis: Voyager encounters a graviton ellipse, a dangerous phenomenon that emerges from subspace on rare occasions.
episodes.title: One Small Step

episodes.synopsis: When Seven of Nine upgrades her Borg alcove to assimilate mass amounts of data, it leads to allegations of conspiracy aboard Voyager.
episodes.title: The Voyager Conspiracy

episodes.synopsis: Back on Earth, Lt. Barclay uses holograms to formulate a plan to open communications with the Voyager.
episodes.title: Pathfinder

episodes.synopsis: The Voyager crew takes part in Paris' latest holodeck getaway in an early 20th century Irish coastal town, where Janeway gets close to a pub owner.
episodes.title: Fair Haven

episodes.synopsis: Voyager is trapped in orbit above a strange planet where time passes thousands of times faster than in the surrounding galaxy.
episodes.title: Blink of an Eye

episodes.synopsis: One species so appreciates the Doctor's singing talent that he considers resigning his commission and staying on with his millions of adoring fans.
episodes.title: Virtuoso

episodes.synopsis: Members of an away mission start dreaming about a species they've never encountered, who are in a gruesome battle on an unknown planet.
episodes.title: Memorial

episodes.synopsis: When Seven of Nine and Tuvok are kidnapped while on an away mission, Seven is forced to fight in a gladiatorial competition -- to the death.
episodes.title: Tsunkatse

episodes.synopsis: Several Borg children abduct Chakotay, Kim, Neelix and Paris.
episodes.title: Collective

episodes.synopsis: Revisiting the holographic town of Fair Haven proves dangerous for Paris and Kim as program characters see Voyager crewmembers alter program elements.
episodes.title: Spirit Folk

episodes.synopsis: Crewmember Lyndsay Ballard, who died on an away mission and was given a traditional burial in space three years earlier, resurfaces.
episodes.title: Ashes to Ashes

episodes.synopsis: Seven of Nine should be overjoyed after Icheb's parents are located, but she's suspicious when told about his original assimilation's circumstances.
episodes.title: Child's Play

episodes.synopsis: In Seven's assessment of ship-wide efficiency, she brings to the captain's attention three "black sheep" crewmen who've slipped through the cracks.
episodes.title: Good Shepherd

episodes.synopsis: A clever trio of identity thieves claiming to be Janeway, Chakotay and Tuvok makes trades all over the quadrant and gives Voyager a bad name.
episodes.title: Live Fast and Prosper

episodes.synopsis: When Kim and B'Elanna take the Delta Flyer in search of dilithium, they crash-land on a prewarp planet, where B'Elanna is found by a local poet.
episodes.title: Muse

episodes.synopsis: Kes returns to Voyager. Aged, angry and more powerful than ever, she tears through the ship and then travels back in time to try to alter her history.
episodes.title: Fury

episodes.synopsis: The Pathfinder project makes use of a pulsar and the Midas Array, allowing a data stream to reach Voyager -- and the ship to reply -- every 32 days.
episodes.title: Life Line

episodes.synopsis: Neelix becomes extremely agitated as Voyager begins a full shutdown before entering a peculiar astronomical nebula.
episodes.title: The Haunting of Deck Twelve

episodes.synopsis: Janeway sees an opportunity to disrupt the Borg when Seven of Nine visits a virtual world where drones retain their individuality for a short time.
episodes.title: Unimatrix Zero: Part 1

episodes.synopsis: Unimatrix Zero is a virtual world where drones can exist free of the Borg collective and free of their biomechanical and cortical implants.
episodes.title: Unimatrix Zero: Part 2

episodes.synopsis: Seven of Nine's life is threatened when her cortical implants begin to degrade. Icheb wants to help her, but his proposition is very risky.
episodes.title: Imperfection

episodes.synopsis: With Janeway's approval, Paris enters the Delta Flyer in an interspecies, light-speed shuttle race held as a peace celebration.
episodes.title: Drive

episodes.synopsis: Security officer Tuvok is investigating a strange series of attacks on Voyager directed at the former Maquis members.
episodes.title: Repression

episodes.synopsis: The Doctor is kidnapped from Voyager by an alien who sells him and his mobile emitter to a hospital on densely-populated planet.
episodes.title: Critical Care

episodes.synopsis: Direct from Starfleet, a hologram of Barclay arrives with instructions to get Voyager home within three days.
episodes.title: Inside Man

episodes.synopsis: When attacked by a species that detests holographic beings, Seven downloads the Doctor's program into her implants.
episodes.title: Body and Soul

episodes.synopsis: Going to the aid of a medical transport, Harry Kim gets his first command.
episodes.title: Nightingale

episodes.synopsis: The Hirogen species sends Voyager a distress call when their holographic prey become too cunning and cannot be defeated.
episodes.title: Flesh & Blood: Parts 1 & 2

episodes.synopsis: After an accident, Chakotay is able to pass through the time spheres that are scattered about the ship after Voyager goes through a temporal rift.
episodes.title: Shattered

episodes.synopsis: Tom and B'Elanna are overjoyed about their coming child, though B'Elanna starts having nightmare flashbacks of her own childhood.
episodes.title: Lineage

episodes.synopsis: Voyager rescues a prison warden and a set of prisoners that are scheduled to be executed, testing their own ethical beliefs.
episodes.title: Repentance

episodes.synopsis: Voyager finds a Klingon ship that left the Alpha Quadrant 80 years before. When they hear of B'Elanna's child they claim that it is their savior.
episodes.title: Prophecy

episodes.synopsis: Voyager slips into a pocket of subspace where many other ships are trapped and must steal from each other to survive.
episodes.title: The Void

episodes.synopsis: Upon returning from a mission, Chakotay, Kim and Neelix find Voyager abandoned and the Doctor the only crew member aboard.
episodes.title: Workforce: Part 1

episodes.synopsis: Upon returning from a mission, Chakotay, Kim and Neelix find Voyager abandoned and the Doctor the only crew member aboard.
episodes.title: Workforce: Part 2

episodes.synopsis: Using the holodeck, Seven of Nine is trying to perfect her social skills to the point of becoming an obsession.
episodes.title: Human Error

episodes.synopsis: When Q finds his son too much to handle he lets Capt. Janeway have a crack at him.
episodes.title: Q2

episodes.synopsis: During their now-regular communications with Earth and Starfleet, the Doctor sends to Earth a holonovel based too closely on his adventures.
episodes.title: Author, Author

episodes.synopsis: For the first time in six years Voyager gets a mission from Starfleet Command: retreive the 21st-century probe Friendship One from a nearby planet.
episodes.title: Friendship One

episodes.synopsis: Chakotay and Seven of Nine's shuttle is crippled by an energy field and they crash on a planet inhabited by a primitive species.
episodes.title: Natural Law

episodes.synopsis: Voyager finds a colony of Talaxians far from their home planet. When Neelix begins to bond with them he makes a major decision.
episodes.title: Homestead

episodes.synopsis: The Doctor abducts and impersonates various members of the crew when the Captain is kidnapped.
episodes.title: Renaissance Man

episodes.synopsis: Ten years after Voyager's return form a 23-year journey across the galaxy, Admiral Janeway breaks all the temporal rules and journeys back in time.
episodes.title: Endgame: Parts 1 & 2
